25. Robertus] (†1536), the head of the house of De la Marck3 see p. 168. The negotiations which led up to the treaty of St. Trond were probably now in progress. After reverting to France in 1521 Robert was crippled by the Burgundians, but was too powerful to be entirely crushed. See BN. xiii. 542-7. He married in 1491 Catherine of the Chimay branch of the family of Croy, niece of the late Bp. of Cam-

bray (Ep. 497 introd.). In dedicating the Paraphrase on Galatians‚ c. April 1519, to their son Antony, canon of hege, Erasmus extols the virtues of both parents (Ep. 956).
